        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Are AI website builders HIPAA compliant?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Most AI website builders (Squarespace, Wix, Framer) are NOT HIPAA-compliant by default. HIPAA requires a Business Associate Agreement (BAA) for handling protected health information. Standard contact forms and booking systems on these platforms are not suitable for collecting medical data. For HIPAA compliance, you need: (1) BAA from your platform provider, (2) Encrypted data storage and transmission, (3) Audit controls, (4) Access controls. Many healthcare providers use AI builders for general information, scheduling, and marketing, then use secure patient portals (SimplePractice, DrChrono, Kareo) for actual health data and patient communication.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What features should healthcare websites include?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Healthcare websites need: (1) Clear contact information with click-to-call phone, (2) Online appointment booking or request forms, (3) Provider bios and credentials, (4) Service descriptions and treatments, (5) Patient resources and forms, (6) Insurance information accepted, (7) Location and hours with maps, (8) Emergency information, (9) Patient testimonials (with permission), (10) Telehealth portal links. For HIPAA compliance, avoid collecting detailed medical information through standard website forms. Use secure patient portals for protected health information.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How much does a healthcare website cost?</h3>
