        </div>

        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Should healthcare providers use AI-generated content?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">AI-generated content works well for basic healthcare website pages: About sections, service descriptions, provider bio templates, FAQ content. However, medical information requires accuracy and oversight. Best practice: Use AI to draft content, have medical professionals review for accuracy. Never let AI generate specific medical advice, treatment protocols, or dosage information. Liability concerns are real. Patients act on medical information found on your website. One error could lead to harm. AI is your content assistant, not your medical authority. Always verify, always review, always have qualified medical staff approve content before publishing.</p>
        </div>

